article.headline: New Mexico State 84, Denver 77
article.story: DENVER (AP) -- Reserve Duane John scored 22 points and four other New Mexico State players reached double figures in defeating Denver 84-77 on Monday night. James Moore had 13 points and nine rebounds and Kelsey Crooks and Byron Davis had 12 points each for New Mexico State (13-12, 6-7 Sun Belt Conference). "We had a solid effort from everybody (Monday)," NMSU coach Lou Henson said. "We need everyone to chip in every night in order for us to win. I think we really played a good game and it was a much needed win for us." Rodney Billups had 26 points and Brett Starkey 16 points and seven rebounds for Denver (14-11, 6-7). The loss kept the Pioneers from clinching one of the eight spots in the upcoming Sun Belt Conference Tournament that begins March 6 in Bowling Green, Ky. The Aggies extended their 10-point lead at the break to 52-38 on Gary Jackson's 3-pointer with 13:38 left, but Billups' layup capped a 6-0 run to get Denver within 52-44. John scored six of the next eight points for New Mexico State and a 62-51 lead. Denver's Erik Benzel, who was 2-for-13 on 3-pointers hit a 3-pointer with 5:03 left to make it 64-53. New Mexico State sealed the win hitting 15-of-17 free throws in the last two minutes. New Mexico State made 6-of-9 shots and outscored Denver 18-5 over the final 8:50 of the first half to lead 40-30. Starkey put Denver ahead 25-22 with a fadeaway jumper, but the Pioneers managed only a free throw by Starkey as over five minutes. While Denver struggled through an 0-for-8 shooting stretch, John scored seven points and Crooks five in a 14-1 run that put the Aggies up 36-26. New Mexico State finished the half shooting 61 percent. "Duane did tremendous for us tonight," Henson said. "His 22 points off the bench lifted our team. He and Frazier really led our team tonight."
